<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-07T08:16:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-07T08:16:00-05:00" n="61" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d61">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/2291</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Roumania, Servia, and Bulgaria</hi>
                                (<persName corresp="#p_VCJ1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Vopicka</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bucharest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-07T15:00:00+01:44">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 7, 1915, 3 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 8, 7 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Roumanian Government, influenced by recent Russian reverses, may remain
                            neutral. It is questionable now whether Roumania will join the Quadruple
                            Entente even if its demands are granted.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_VCJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Vopicka</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>